        "text": "Collaboration patterns for doing the actual work (e.g. a User Story that has dependencies or requires the involvement of another team) can be staggered (with gaps in between), sequential, or parallel. Coordination can be done by exception (when a problem manifests itself) or on a permanent basis by teams' representatives, or by all team members. Priorities can be arbitrated and orchestrated externally, negotiated internally by the teams involved, or agreed upon collaboratively by all teams involved. It is the nature of the work and the ability of the teams that lead to a solution that is good. The way to find what works is described in section J of the [[Principle 7 - Scale experimenting-learning-adapting-evolving guided by Complexity, Lean and Agile]].\n"
