      "item": {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "id": "8cd581475f06dd18",
        "text": "Trying to ”manage” collaboration and its improvement directly is likely to lead to worse collaboration such as traditional Programme Management techniques. It is more effective to approach the problem in an oblique way, doing cross-team building as we do team-building. The team member that has good social skills, a tendency to look at the big picture, a good knowledge of the company and the code-base, and a view of the dependencies that the team is facing in the coming Sprints/Iterations can be the good cross-team facilitator that is needed or can work in pair with the appointed facilitator.\n\n"
